history.content:
If you're planning on becoming a Data Scientist, it seems like a great class to take (from personal experience) as it teaches you practical, relevant concepts such as data visualization and cleaning, feature engineering, SQL (186 teaches more advanced stuff), modeling (189 teaches more advanced stuff) and gives you experience with common tools like pandas, sklearn, matplotlib/seaborn, etc. 

Whether it's worth taking instead of another class depends on which ones you're comparing it to since one could argue a lot of Data 100 material could be learned easily via hands-on experience outside of a class.

Would anyone recommend taking data 100 after having taken 189? I'm graduating in fall next semester and am not sure if it be worth taking instead of another class. I do plan to work as a data scientist of some sort after graduating if that makes any difference.
history.subject: Data 100 after CS 189?
